Alahli Takaful, Petrochem, Thimar: Saudi Arabian Equity Preview

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-12-10T07:58:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-10/alahli-takaful-petrochem-thimar-saudi-arabian-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Saudi Arabia’s market. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  The  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  rose 0.6 percent to 6,251.92 on
Dec. 7.  Alahli Takaful Co. (ATC)  : The Saudi insurance company
said its sold 6.6 million shares to existing shareholders
compared with offers of 8.5 million. The shares dropped 0.7
percent to 70.25 riyals.  National Agriculture Marketing Co. (THIMAR)  : The company
known as Thimar said its board recommended the company’s capital
be cut by half to 50 million riyals ($13 million) to write off
losses. The shares rose 2.9 percent to 19.05 riyals.  Saudi National Petrochemical Co. (PETROCH)  : The company
also known as Petrochem said its joint venture with Arabian
Chevron Phillips Petrochemical Co. is expected to start up its
Jubail plant for commercial production in the first quarter. The
shares rose 0.7 percent to 22.15 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
